    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="706"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d706">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24/1715</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Chief of the China Division of the Foreign Economic
                        Administration</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McCann</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Adviser to the Liberated Areas
                        Division</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moffat</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-23">April 23,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Moffat</hi>: The enclosed<note n="13a"
                        xml:id="d706fn13a">Not printed.</note> covers the first specific request
                    through Universal Trading Corporation for used commercial industrial equipment
                    to be purchased and held for post war shipment.</p>
                <p>Universal Trading Corporation are as you know the Chinese Government cash
                    purchase agency in this country.</p>
                <p>We shall be interested in State Department’s opinion as to the desirability of
                    sponsoring this and similar requests. This is a commercial transaction—no
                    request is made for Lend-Lease aid.</p>
                <p>Were shipment desired at this time we would register objection on the grounds
                    that such material will only further congest warehousing facilities in
                    India.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">R. E. McCann</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
